In our case the “Sale”‐type transactions are the only ones that contribute to the “main business revenue” category.

Now we sum them step‐by‐step:

• After row 7: 6443119.59 + 1022251.53 = 7465371.12  
• After row 8: 7465371.12 + 643496.33 = 8108867.45  
• After row 9: 8108867.45 + 2100055.92 = 10208923.37  
• After row 10: 10208923.37 + 628501.63 = 10837425.00  
• After row 11: 10837425.00 + 1418227.07 = 12255652.07  
• After row 12: 12255652.07 + 681971.04 = 12937623.11  
• After row 13: 12937623.11 + 627921.21 = 13565544.32  
• After row 14: 13565544.32 + 2003755.19 = 15569299.51  

The sum of the “after_tax_amount” from all sales is 15,569,299.51. This value represents the net revenue from the main business (the sales).

Thus, the “Main Business Revenue” item is 15,569,299.51.
